examples:
[{"name":"Using a for loop to perform a set number of actions","code":"```
for(int i = 0; i < 5; i++)
{
     System.out.println(i);
}
```
//the output indicates how the value of i changes with each iteration of the loop 

//when i is equal to 5, it no longer satisfies the condition anymore and therefore  the body of the loop is not executed

**output:**

0

1

2

3

4
"},{"name":"Using a for loop to iterate through an array","description":"","code":"a `for loop` can be used to iterate through the elements of a pre-defined array 
```
int [] numbers = {1, 2, 3, 4};
for(int i =0; i < numbers.length(); i++)
{
     System.out.println(numbers[i]);
}
```
**output:**

1

2

3

4
"}]

syntax:
for (initialExpression; testExpression; updateExpression) {

    // body of code
}

